NAME
       fcoeadm - Fibre Channel over Ethernet (FCoE) user space tool

SYNOPSIS
       fcoeadm  [[--create|-c] | [--destroy|-d] | [--query|-q]] <ifname> 
       fcoeadm  [--help | -h]

DESCRIPTION
       Creates, destroys, or queries FCoE instance on a given netword interface.

OPTIONS
       --create, -c <ifname>
	   Creates a FCoE instance based on the givne <ifname>. It first checks
	   the existence of /sys/module/fcoe first to check if fcoe module is
	   loaded. The <ifname> is then written to /sys/module/fcoe/create.

       --destroy, -d <ifname>
 	   Destroys a FCoE instance based on the givne <ifname>. It first checks
	   the existence of /sys/module/fcoe first to check if fcoe module is
	   loaded. The <ifname> is then written to /sys/module/fcoe/destroy.

       --query, -q <ifname>
           Queries basic FCoE information for the given <ifname>. It looks for the
	   corresponding fc_host un /sys/class/fc_host. When such fc_host is
	   found for the <ifname>, basic information suchs world wide port name,
	   world wide node name, fabric name, etc., will be dispalyed.

       --help, -h
           Display this help information.

       <ifname>
           The network interface name, such as eth0, eth1, etc.

EXAMPLES
       Create a FCoE instance on eth2

               $ fcoeadm --create eth2

       Destroy a FCoE instance on eth2

               $ fcoeadm --destroy eth2
       
       Query FCoE information on eth2
	
               $ fcoeadm --query eth2

